    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not assessed per MRL 2 scoping, consistent with ASME V&V 40-2018 guidance. Validation results demonstrate CFD predictions of hemolysis index and hydraulic performance within acceptable agreement bounds across the COU operating envelope. The RH < 1 acceptance criterion is satisfied at all five operating points. The overall credibility body of evidence is sufficient to support the decision to accept the CFD model for identifying worst-case hemolysis conditions in the CPB application.",
